Former Celtic goalkeeper Pat Bonner on Kieran Tierney to #AFC: &ldquo;If Kieran was playing in England, he'd probably be worth about &pound;50m, but because it's Scotland, I would think &pound;25m would be a price you'd start talking about, with add-ons.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Bonner: &ldquo;He's got the ability to go into a club like #AFC. Whether Arsenal is a big enough club for Kieran Tierney, that's the question. If you were picking out a player in British football atm that can play LB, himself &amp; Andy Robertson are the best two in UK, if not Europe.&quot;
